tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured parameters are within normal limits. Glycemic control (HbA1c, glucose), renal function (urea, creatinine), electrolytes, lipid profile, and calcium are all unremarkable. No laboratory evidence of metabolic, renal, or lipid abnormalities at this time. No further action required from a laboratory perspective.
